 that socio-technical resources are key factors in understanding migration flows and migrant-home relations. Overall, this book provides rare insights into the rural side of migration and farmers' knowledge and agency.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 4aAnthropology. 4aAsian Studies. 4aDevelopment Studies. 4aEast Asia and North East Asia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh  aChina, rural-urban migration, knowledge and skill, rice farming, migrant-left-behind nexus.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074322708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048552184zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048552184zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048552184.jpg  a978-3-11-074322-7 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7 DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075418-6 EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-